The paper deals with the syntactic complexity of regular languages, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). It also introduces new types of aperiodic transition semigroups, which is a topic in algebraic automata theory (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the structure of these semigroups, which involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic concepts (cs.LO, cs.GT). Finally, the paper touches on the state complexity of certain operations on regular languages, which is a topic in automata theory and control theory (cs.SY).
